      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aY",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1864321833,
      "version": 672,
      "versionNonce": 1341434729,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1766000117994,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Consolidate Sales\n- Assume Sales1 and Sales2 are no longer used and all updates will go to Sales3\n- business_key = SalesOrderNumber + SalesOrderLineNumber\n    - Rationale:  This pair uniquely identifies each line item within a sales order, which aligns with how businesses typically track individual transactions\n    - It's meaningful across systems, stable over time, and avoids relying on surrogate keys like OnlineSalesKey that may not exist outside the database\n    - Since SalesOrderNumber and SalesOrderLineNumber is highly correlated, only use SalesOrderNumber as a cluster by key\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Consolidate Sales\n- Assume Sales1 and Sales2 are no longer used and all updates will go to Sales3\n- business_key = SalesOrderNumber + SalesOrderLineNumber\n    - Rationale:  This pair uniquely identifies each line item within a sales order, which aligns with how businesses typically track individual transactions\n    - It's meaningful across systems, stable over time, and avoids relying on surrogate keys like OnlineSalesKey that may not exist outside the database\n    - Since SalesOrderNumber and SalesOrderLineNumber is highly correlated, only use SalesOrderNumber as a cluster by key\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
